                            <comment id="12621501" author="dajevu" created="Mon, 11 Aug 2008 16:51:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Large XML file I was attempting to process&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12623951" author="dinuka" created="Wed, 20 Aug 2008 10:38:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Jeff,&lt;br/&gt;
      Would you able to add the stack trace when you get this error ?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12625995" author="dinuka" created="Wed, 27 Aug 2008 07:42:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Jeff,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;         I tested the same payload using http rather than vfs and it worked fine without any error. I believe it is an issue with VFS Transport. Will be looking into this and will keep you updated.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12627252" author="veithen" created="Sat, 30 Aug 2008 20:54:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is due to a bug in VFSTransportListener: the VFS input stream is closed before handleIncomingMessage is called. Note that this bug only affects XML payloads (not text/plain and application/octet-stream). Corrected in trunk.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
